From fd620b50efab6903f24e5ff91181b168b483e002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Ryan X. Charles" <ryan@ryanxcharles.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 13:21:40 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Round outer split borders to window corner radius

Use UnevenRoundedRectangle for split pane borders: outer corners
match NSWindow _cornerRadius (fallback 10), inner content/dim clip
at R-w. Window-edge flags come from the split tree so internal
T-junctions stay square.
---
 .../Splits/TerminalSplitTreeView.swift        | 33 +++++++--
 .../Ghostty/Surface View/InspectorView.swift  |  6 +-
 .../Ghostty/Surface View/SurfaceView.swift    | 67 ++++++++++++++++++-
 3 files changed, 98 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/macos/Sources/Features/Splits/TerminalSplitTreeView.swift b/macos/Sources/Features/Splits/TerminalSplitTreeView.swift
